President Obama released a statement on the 50th anniversary of Head Start, highlighting its importance in providing a better life for millions of families and children. He emphasized the need to strengthen and expand Head Start, increasing access to its programs and partnering with child care centers to reach more infants and toddlers. The President also called on Congress and leaders at all levels to support Head Start and invest in early childhood education, stating that it is one of the smartest investments for America's future. He thanked everyone who has contributed to the success of Head Start and urged continued support to ensure its service to families for the next 50 years and beyond, emphasizing that every child in America deserves a head start in life.